reviews.reviewText: One of the dinosaurs didn't light up when I first opened the package but the rest were very nice and lit up very brightly, so no big deal. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Very cute, but batteries die. Now what
reviews.reviewText: My granddaughter could not have loved these dinosaurs more. They're very cute, small, and they light up when they touch the water and they stop lighting up when they're dry. Unfortunately, they didn't last very long, they varied -some lasted a couple of weeks and Some lasted over a month but they all died. Apparently, the batteries can't be replaced and now they're just plastic toys --which would have been great if they started out that way, but she expects a lot more now. They are a disappointment to her.Pro tip, dry them off and don't put them on a damp surface so they don't light up when the kids not using them and the battery will last a little longer.
